    <h1>POS for POS users</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>On this page, you will find detailed information about how to operate a plentymarkets POS.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="5">1. Installing the plentymarkets app</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>To get started, install the plentymarkets App on your mobile device.</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong><a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=eu.plentymarkets.mobile&amp;hl=en" target="_blank" rel="noopener">plentymarkets App in Google Play</a></strong></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong><a href="https://itunes.apple.com/en/app/plentymarkets/id957702618" target="_blank" rel="noopener">plentymarkets App in iTunes</a></strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock warning">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-warning" title="Warning"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Offline orders are deleted when you uninstall the app</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If your internet connection is down, POS orders are saved on your device and uploaded to plentymarkets once connection returns. If you uninstall the app on your device before all orders were uploaded to plentymarkets, the orders saved on your device are deleted permanently and cannot be recovered by you or the plentymarkets support team. As such, check that no offline orders exist on your device before uninstalling the app.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="10">2. Logging into plentymarkets POS</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as described below to log into plentymarkets POS.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Logging into plentymarkets POS:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Log into your mobile device.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>On the start screen, tap the plentymarkets App icon.<br>
→ The login screen is displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter your login details. Note <a href="#table-POS-users-login">Table 1</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Tap <strong>Log in</strong>.<br>
→ The start screen of the plentymarkets App is displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Tap the menu symbol at the top left of the screen.<br>
→ The menu is displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Tap <strong>POS</strong>.<br>
→ plentymarkets POS opens.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Login details are saved</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You will remain logged in to plentymarkets POS until you tap <strong>Log out</strong> in the app menu. That means that you can open and close the app without having to log in again.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
